.TH "git alias.finishto(1) User manual" "" "April, 2020" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
git finishto
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
git finishto branch - rebase to first argument, fast forward merge, then
delete first argument
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
git finishto is a helper alias to rebase HEAD onto another branch and
then delete that branch.
.IP "1." 3
Ensures that the current HEAD is not a detached HEAD
.IP "2." 3
Ensures that the proper number of arguments have been provided
.IP "3." 3
Stores the ref of HEAD so it can be deleted at the end
.IP "4." 3
Ensures that the provided argument is associated with a branch
.IP "5." 3
Calls the rebaseto alias to rebase the changesets to the target branch
.IP "6." 3
Calls the mergeto alias to fast-forward merge the HEAD with the target
branch
.IP "7." 3
Deletes the branch since it is not no longer needed
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
git finishto $(git brupstream)
.IP \[bu] 2
git finishto master
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
finishfrom rebaseto mergeto
.SH DETAILS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
finishto = \[dq]!f() { : git man finishto; \[rs]
    if ! git symbolic-ref HEAD; then echo \[aq]on detached head\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    [ $# -ne 1 ] && echo \[aq]Usage: finishto branch\[aq] && return 1; \[rs]
    PREV=$(git symbolic-ref HEAD | cut -d/ -f3-); \[rs]
    if ! git show-ref $1; then echo \[aq]branch not a named ref\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    git rebaseto $1; \[rs]
    git mergeto $1; \[rs]
    git branch -d $PREV; \[rs]
}; f\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
